[2026-07-04] Task 3D - MERGE CONFIRMED, Tier 3 FULLY CLOSED
Task 3D's adversarial review found a real BLOCKING issue: the inbound
rate limiter keyed strictly on session_id, but session middleware
mints a fresh session for any cookie-less request, so the limiter
never actually engaged for a caller that simply never sends a cookie -
30 requests via 30 fresh clients all returned 200 against a 10/minute
cap. This defeated Sec10.5's entire purpose and survived two rounds of
tester verification, since those tests only exercised the fallback key
function in isolation, never the live-stack attack path. Fixed by
making IP (via slowapi's get_remote_address) the primary, unconditional
key, with session_id demoted to a secondary dimension for finer-grained
same-IP limiting. Both tester and adversarial-generalist independently
re-attempted the exact original attack against the fix and confirmed
it's closed - adversarial additionally tried and ruled out an
X-Forwarded-For spoofing bypass (not trusted anywhere in the app) and
a trailing-slash route-matching bypass (redirects to the canonical,
rate-limited path). A second, non-blocking finding (streaming-response
mid-generation exceptions can't be retroactively converted to a safe
error shape once headers are flushed) was honestly documented as an
accepted limitation rather than oversold as fixed, plus server-side
logging was added so a real failure isn't silent.
Two minor items carried forward, not blockers: the new IP-keying has
no reverse-proxy/X-Forwarded-For awareness - correct for today's
direct-to-host deployment but needs revisiting at Task 5A if a reverse
proxy is introduced; and no test yet forces the export.py logging
wrapper to actually fire on a real mid-stream exception (coverage gap,
not a correctness gap).
Tier 3 (Wave 1: 3A/3B/3C, Wave 2: 3D) is now FULLY CLOSED - every task
independently verified by tester and adversarial-generalist, every
real finding fixed and re-verified with revert-reproduce-restore rigor.

